&lt;h1 id=&#34;energy-band--charge-carriers&#34;&gt;Energy Band &amp;amp; Charge Carriers&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;energy-band-formation&#34;&gt;Energy band Formation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When atoms combine to form substances, the outermost shells, subshells and orbitals merge, providing a greater number of available energy levels for electrons to assume.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When large numbers of atoms are close to each other, these available energy levels form a &lt;strong&gt;nearly continuous band&lt;/strong&gt; wherein electrons may move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;interatomic-spacing--category&#34;&gt;Interatomic spacing &amp;amp; Category&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equilibrium&lt;/strong&gt;: 即$r = r_0$处，两个原子的吸引力与排斥力相抵消&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band分类&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
